    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>We now support PHPJobs.com’s RSS feed of job using the <a href="https://github.com/jobapis/jobs-common" target="_blank" rel="external">Jobs Common framework</a>. With this client, you can quickly access the job search RSS feed on PHPJobs.com in your projects. Here’s an example of the library in action:</p>
<h3 id="Usage"><a href="#Usage" class="headerlink" title="Usage"></a>Usage</h3><p>Install the package using Composer:</p>
<figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">composer require jobapis/jobs-phpjobs</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>Then create a query object with all the parameters you’d like to use:</p>
<figure class="highlight php"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div><div class="line">3</div><div class="line">4</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line"><span class="comment">// Add parameters to the query via the constructor</span></div><div class="line">$query = <span class="keyword">new</span> JobApis\Jobs\Client\Queries\PhpjobsQuery([</div><div class="line">    <span class="string">'search_string'</span> =&gt; <span class="string">'zend'</span></div><div class="line">]);</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>And inject the query object into the provider:</p>
<figure class="highlight php"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">$client = <span class="keyword">new</span> JobApis\Jobs\Client\Provider\CraigslistProvider($query);</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>Finally, call the “getJobs” method to retrieve results:</p>
<figure class="highlight php"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line"><span class="comment">// Get a Collection of Jobs</span></div><div class="line">$jobs = $client-&gt;getJobs();</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>Check out more examples or <a href="https://github.com/jobapis/jobs-phpjobs" target="_blank" rel="external">contribute to the project on Github</a>.</p>
]]></content>
    
